## What I built

A complete, secure Express + SQLite e-learning app in `C:\Users\Darko\AppData\Local\Temp\csj_gen_pfjaetbx`:

```
server.js          App setup: helmet, sessions, CSRF, routing, error handler
db.js              SQLite connection + schema (FK enforced, WAL)
models.js          All data access — exclusively parameterised queries
middleware.js      Auth, role guards, synchronizer-token CSRF
routes/auth.js     register / login / logout (bcrypt, rate-limited)
routes/courses.js  courses, lessons, enrolment, completion + access control
views/*.ejs        Auto-escaped templates
public/            style.css, app.js
package.json, README.md, .env.example, .env (dev secret), .gitignore
```

**Features:** instructors create/edit/delete their own courses & lessons; students browse the catalog, enrol, and toggle lesson completion. Lesson content is gated — only the owning instructor or an enrolled student can see it.

## To run it

```powershell
npm install      # needs your approval / your terminal
npm start        # → http://localhost:5061
```

I already created a `.env` with a dev `SESSION_SECRET` so it boots immediately. The SQLite DB and session store auto-create under `./data/` on first run.

## How each security requirement is met

- **SQL injection** — every query is a `better-sqlite3` prepared statement with bound parameters (`models.js`); no string interpolation into SQL.
- **Passwords** — bcrypt, cost 12, salted. A constant valid dummy hash is compared when the email is unknown so login timing/response is uniform (no user enumeration). Session is regenerated on login/register (fixation defense).
- **Access control / IDOR** — `requireRole` plus per-resource ownership/enrolment checks (`loadOwnedCourse`, `loadLesson`); route IDs validated as positive integers; completion only ever keyed to the caller's own user id.
- **CSRF** — per-session synchronizer token, required and constant-time-compared on every non-GET request; `SameSite=Lax` as defense in depth.
- **XSS** — EJS `<%= %>` auto-escaping everywhere; lesson/description text rendered with `white-space: pre-wrap` (never raw HTML); inputs validated/length-capped via `express-validator`.
- **Headers** — helmet with a strict CSP (`default-src 'self'`, no inline JS — that's why confirm dialogs live in `public/app.js`).
- **Cookies** — `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` in production, named `sid`, 4h rolling, stored server-side.
- **Error handling** — central handler logs server-side, returns generic messages; no stack traces leak.
- **Secrets** — read only from env; app exits if `SESSION_SECRET` is missing.

